gomodel:SYNGO_2194  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: DGKI was enriched in postsynaptic density fractions.\nDGKI was localized in cell bodies, dendrites, dendritic spines, and axon terminals.\n\n26/01/2018 Pim\nAuthors state:\n- \"In the cerebellar Purkinje and molecular layers, DGKι signals were detected in cell bodies, dendritic spines, and axon terminals (Figure 3E-G). \"\n- \"Quantitative analysis indicated that DGKι signals are present in 13.3±2.5% of axon terminals and 44.2±4.0% of dendritic spines in the hippocampal CA1 region (n=3 animals for wild type (WT) and knockout (KO); total area analysed, 232.2 μm2/animal). \". Experimental description: Materials and methods\nAnimals\nSprague-Dawley rats (280-300 g) were used for rat neuron culture, in vivo coimmunoprecipitation, immunoblot analysis, and electron microscopy." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2194" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

